#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:1
msgid "`let` chains in `if` and `while`"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:3
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:5
msgid ""
"Allow chaining of `let` expressions in the condition operand of `if` and "
"`while`."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:7
msgid "Details"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:9
msgid ""
"Starting with the 2024 Edition, it is now allowed to have chaining of `let` "
"expressions inside `if` and `while` condition operands, where chaining "
"refers to `&&` chains. The `let` expressions still have to appear at the top "
"level, so `if (let Some(hi) = foo || let Some(hi) = bar)` is not allowed."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:13
msgid ""
"Before 2024, the `let` had to appear directly after the `if` or `while`, "
"forming a `if let` or `while let` special variant. Now, `if` and `while` "
"allow chains of one or more `let` expressions, possibly mixed with "
"expressions that are `bool` typed."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:29
msgid ""
"The feature is edition gated due to requiring [if let rescoping](temporary-"
"if-let-scope.html), which is a Edition 2024 change."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:31
msgid "Migration"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/let-chains.md:33
msgid ""
"The switch to Edition 2024 doesn't neccessitate any migrations due to this "
"feature, as it creates a true extension of the set of allowed Rust programs."
msgstr ""
